{"parse":{"title":"Sifa","pageid":20830372,"revid":829477646,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">This article is about a safety device in a train. For other uses, see <a href=\"/wiki/Sifa_(disambiguation)\" class=\"mw-redirect mw-disambig\" title=\"Sifa (disambiguation)\">Sifa (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:202px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:SIFA-Pedal.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/61/SIFA-Pedal.jpg/200px-SIFA-Pedal.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"133\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/61/SIFA-Pedal.jpg/300px-SIFA-Pedal.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/61/SIFA-Pedal.jpg/400px-SIFA-Pedal.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1000\" data-file-height=\"667\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:SIFA-Pedal.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A Sifa pedal in an <a href=\"/wiki/InterCity\" title=\"InterCity\">InterCity</a> driving car. On its right is the foot button for the <a href=\"/wiki/Train_horn\" title=\"Train horn\">train horn</a></div></div></div>\n<p><b>Sifa</b> is a type of <a href=\"/wiki/Deadman%27s_switch#Trains\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Deadman&#39;s switch\">deadman's control system</a> used on German-influenced European railroads.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  Although <a href=\"/wiki/Deadman%27s_switch#Trains\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Deadman&#39;s switch\">deadman's pedals</a> are commonly used on railroads worldwide, Sifa systems are specifically those codified by <a href=\"/wiki/DIN\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"DIN\">German Industrial Norms</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Verband_der_Elektrotechnik,_Elektronik_und_Informationstechnik\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Verband der Elektrotechnik, Elektronik und Informationstechnik\">VDE</a> 0119-207-5.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Description\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Description</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Description\">Description</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Sifa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Description\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Sifa is short for <i>Sicherheitsfahrschaltung</i>, German for \"safety driving switch\". It is usually a pedal and/or large press button, which monitors the alertness of the driver. The driver has to repeatedly press a button after a fixed interval; if he fails to do so, the train will carry out an emergency-stop. It complements the external train safety systems: <a href=\"/wiki/Punktf%C3%B6rmige_Zugbeeinflussung\" title=\"Punktf\u00f6rmige Zugbeeinflussung\">PZB</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Linienzugbeeinflussung\" title=\"Linienzugbeeinflussung\">LZB</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/European_Train_Control_System\" title=\"European Train Control System\">ETCS</a>.\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:202px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Sifa_ice3.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/Sifa_ice3.jpg/200px-Sifa_ice3.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"150\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/Sifa_ice3.jpg/300px-Sifa_ice3.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/Sifa_ice3.jpg/400px-Sifa_ice3.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"640\" data-file-height=\"480\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Sifa_ice3.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Sifa control display in the <a href=\"/wiki/ICE_3\" title=\"ICE 3\">ICE 3</a></div></div></div>\n<p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Europe\" title=\"Europe\">Europe</a> the <i>Zeit-Zeit-Sifa</i> (time-time Sifa) is common. In this system, the engine driver holds a pedal or button down for 30 seconds and must then briefly release the pressure. Thus the system can confirm that the driver is still able to react. If the driver does not react after 30 seconds, the system warns the driver, at first optically, then for a few seconds acoustically. After a further short period of time without any reaction the train is automatically stopped. The <i>Zeit-Weg-Sifa</i> (time-distance Sifa) system takes account of the distance travelled, as well as time, since the last activation.\n</p><p>In electric trains such as those working on <a href=\"/wiki/Rapid_transit_in_Germany#U-Bahn\" title=\"Rapid transit in Germany\">U-</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/S-Bahn\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"S-Bahn\">S-Bahn</a> lines the Sifa has for a long time been combined with the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Driving_switch&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Driving switch (page does not exist)\">driving switch</a>. This is where the concept of the dead man's switch first arose. If the button was released (due to the driver falling asleep) the train was automatically stopped.\n</p><p>In order to test the function of the Sifa the driver must carry out a Sifa test run before the train is used in order to check that the train is automatically braked.\n</p><p>After serious accidents as a result of drivers falling asleep, where the pedal was still regularly activated, the <a href=\"/wiki/Deutsche_Reichsbahn_(GDR)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Deutsche Reichsbahn (GDR)\">Deutsche Reichsbahn</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/East_Germany\" title=\"East Germany\">East Germany</a> introduced a special type of Sifa (<i>Sifa86</i>) into service. Here the driver has to acknowledge, by pressing a button, an optical signal at a time and distance interval randomly generated by the system.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Sifa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Dead_man%27s_switch\" title=\"Dead man&#39;s switch\">Dead man's switch</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Dead-man%27s_vigilance_device\" title=\"Dead-man&#39;s vigilance device\">Dead-man's vigilance device</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Train_protection_system\" title=\"Train protection system\">Train protection system</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Watchdog_timer\" title=\"Watchdog timer\">Watchdog timer</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Emergency_brake_(train)\" title=\"Emergency brake (train)\">Emergency brake</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Parking_brake\" title=\"Parking brake\">Hand brake</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Sifa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.virtualmarket.innotrans.de/index.php5?id=1022238&amp;highlight=&amp;fid=523&amp;offset=0&amp;Action=showProduct\">\"Deadman's control system UDB\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2008-12-24</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Deadman%E2%80%99s+control+system+UDB&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.virtualmarket.innotrans.de%2Findex.php5%3Fid%3D1022238%26highlight%3D%26fid%3D523%26offset%3D0%26Action%3DshowProduct&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASifa\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Sifa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://everything2.com/e2node/Why%2520it%2527s%2520safe%2520to%2520take%2520the%2520train\">Why it's safe to take the train</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1283\nCached time: 20180908055242\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.088 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.114 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 73/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 1648/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 3/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\n